PrecisAuthority (a) to enter into a "SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT" with the Woodland Cree Indian Band No. 474, in the Province of Alberta (composed of indigenous people living in the Cadotte Lake area), which among other things will resolve certain outstanding land claims made pursuant to TREATY No. 8, and (b) to release the Province of Alberta from its obligations pursuant to paragraph 10 of the Constitution Act, 1930.
